title: Charge Dispersion Studies of Heavy-Mass Elements In The Fission of Th-232 By Protons of Medium Energy.

x4freetext: CHARGE DISPERSION STUDIES OF HEAVY-MASS ELEMENTS IN THE
FISSION OF TH-232 BY PROTONS OF MEDIUM ENERGY.
MONITOR IS CORRECTED.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Journal of Inorganic and Nuclear Chemistry, Vol.35, p.3991 (1973)

x4freetext: .OBSERVATIONS ABOUT CHARGE DISPERSION CURVES
AS A FUNCTION OF SINGLE AND MULTICHANCE FISSION.
A TARGET STACK CONSITED OF THREE THORIUM FOILS,
THICKNESS 0.005 CM EACH,AND THREE COPPER FOILS (THE
COPPER FOILS WERE 0.025 CM THICK),THE LATTER PLACED
UPSTREM WITH RESPECT TO THE THORIUM FOILS.ALL SIX FOILS
WERE CAREFULLY ALIGNED,WRAPPED WITH ALUMINUM FOILS
(0.002 CM THICK).
.NAI(TL)CRYSTAL DETECTOR.
.2 CM**3 GE(LI) SEMICONDUCTOR DETECTOR.
ERRORS WERE ESTIMATED TAKING INTO ACCOUNT RANDOM ERRORS
ASSOCIATED WITH DECAY-CURVE ANALYSIS,CHEMICAL YIELDS,
PHOTOPEAKAREA DETERMINATION,AS WELL AS THE SYSTEMATIC
ERRORS ASSOCIATED WITH DETECTOR EFFICIENCIES,SPREAD IN
PROTON BEAM ENERGY,ETC.ERRORS WERE ESTIMATED BY TAKING
THE SQUARE ROOT OF THE SUMS OF THE SQUARES OF THE
INDIVIDAL ERRORS AND WERE FOUND TO BE 10-20 PER CENT IN
MOST CASES.DUPLICATE RESULTS AGREED USUALLY TO 5 PER
CENT,OCCASIONALLY TO 15 PER CENT,EXCEPT IN THE CASE
CE-144 WHICH OCCASIONALLY WERE SLIGHTLY GREATER.HOWEVER
CROSS SECTIONS CALCULATED IN THE CASE OF THE TIMED
DOUBLE-EXTRACTION EXPERIMENTS SHOWED POORER
REPRODUCIBILITY (IN SOME CASES THE VALUES DIFFERED BY
AS MUCH AS 50 PER CENT).THIS INDICATES HOW THE ERRORS
MAY BE PROPAGATED BY THE EXPONENTIAL RELATIONS.
